|passage=Whether it is on the BBC, ITV or commercial radio does not really matter. ...can give you a radio example of two things I was listening to '''at the weekend'''.}}
* {{lb|en|US|Canada}} "on the weekend", "this weekend", "for the weekend" ("at the weekend" is not used)
